<tt>Fri Jan 10 21:23:09 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Well, to continue this string.  My movie was Platoon.  Not so much the characters or the story line but the background just was so real to me.  The shit detail; I can still smell that deisel oil and mixture.  The songs played on the record player in the barracks.  The sounds of the choppers and I could feel like I was there again..  What a rush, what a scary feeling.<br>
When the movie was over (I went by myself) I got into my truck and made it into my driveway.  I sat in the truck and shook and cried for what seemed forever. That it was so real and brought back the sights and sounds.  It was probably the first time that I had recalled anything in depth about my tour. Ever! <br>
Each movie has something different for every vet that I have ever talked to.  For example, Platoon was &quot;my war.&quot;  Other Marines say that Full Metal Jacket depicted their tour. Hell, I was all over the Central Highlands for two years and never saw a building that that was more than a single story.  Hamburger Hill represented a war for others.  <br>
I just wish my war was like John Rambo's when he went in to get others out.  But then that's Hollywood.<br><br>

